The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of vector embeddings to represent images is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of taxonomy and classification in ecology, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
